</span></h3><p class="sc-fIosxK hdNOer pf-52_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-54_">The need to comply with UK legislation and regulations is at the heart of induction training. Key laws such as the Health and Social Care Act 2008, the Care Act 2014, and region-specific regulations in Wales and Scotland set the baseline for training requirements. The Care Quality Commission (CQC) in England, Care Inspectorate Wales, the Scottish Social Services Council, and other regulatory bodies ensure adherence to these standards.
</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-dFtzxp icSyEj pf-55_ _Y6RW61"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-cLpAjG dTtSfA pf-57_">The Care Certificate
